  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Innovation Project: Baby Box for Disaster Risk Reduction (DRR)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Baby Box Innovation Project aims to act as an incentive and tool for individual women and community leaders to prioritize maternal and infant health and safety during disasters through preparedness and health emergency response planning in covered communities.  The Project will (1) ensure easy access to basic newborn health and dignity items, (2) increase access to information on newborn care and reproductive health and (3) strengthen community connection with health services and social networks in the community.  These will be accomplished through the (1) conduct of community -based research, consulting with directly affected community women, partners and LGU officials to gain their input and recommendations on what an effective, useful Baby Box would contain and look like; (2) design and development of a Baby Box prototype and information, education, communications (IEC) materials; and (3) conduct of community education and consultations to validate efficiency and usefulness of the Baby Box.</narrative>
  </description>
